main event: An unidentified aerial object was sighted near Melville, Labrador, Canada on August 6, 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, luminous shape that hovered over the military installation for approximately 45 minutes.
The object emitted a beam of light that illuminated the area around it.
Attempts to detect the object on radar were unsuccessful.
Photographs of the object were taken and are being forwarded for evaluation.
The report states that the sighting will be carried in the Project Blue Book files as Case No. 8489.
sighted object: a bright, luminous object that hovered and emitted a beam of light
witnesses: military personnel and a civilian resident
